How to Install Recorder deamon

1. log as root
2. execute ./install.sh

The script will install the program in /home/recd   

/home/recd
|
|- bin 
|- cfg
|- tools

"bin" subdir will contains recd, recd_d and recd.cron
-recd      : is the deamon compiled in release mode
-recd.cron : used to create a cron job, this script will check for the process recd and if not running it will be executed.

"cfg" subdir will contains recd.cfg 
-recd.cfg  : configuration file for recording deamon

"tools" subdir will contains all tools program
-capture   : it is a program able to save one PNG file from specified source, so usefull during a new installation in order to create the skins.

The install.sh script also create a sub folder in  /etc/ named recd and in that subfolder just a simbolic link to -> recd.cfg

A new user will be added to the system "recd". 
